txt.en: 'You have done a lot of good for a lot of folk, Bounder [placeholder]. Report back to Second Shirriff Bodo Bunce by Town Hole in Michel Delving and tell him of your deeds!'

'I have heard of all the good you have done, [placeholder]. You truly are an excellent Bounder and deserve the thanks of all Shire-folk!\n\n'We don't go in for uniforms, but I must say that you've earned another feather in your cap. Take it with my thanks!'
'Talk to Second Shirriff Bodo Bunce by Town Hole in Michel Delving. He'll be very pleased to hear of all the good you have done!'
You have proven to be a Bounder of great merit.
'You have proven to be quite the Bounder, [placeholder]!'
'You have my thanks for all the good you have done, Bounder [placeholder].'
Second Shirriff Bodo Bunce is by Town Hole in Michel Delving.\n\nYou have been told to bring word of the many good deeds you have performed for the Shire-folk to Bodo Bunce.
